502
00:57:01,745 --> 00:57:07,838
You also don't really need a peer review for every one of those statutory local concerns.

503
00:57:08,779 --> 00:57:10,002
I just want to jump in on this.

504
00:57:10,975 --> 00:57:11,696
Yeah, yeah, go ahead, Judy.

505
00:57:11,736 --> 00:57:18,380
The board is not obligated to make a finding of fact on every local concern in the statute.

506
00:57:18,941 --> 00:57:24,905
The local concerns are there to sort of define the bounds of the board's jurisdiction.

507
00:57:25,625 --> 00:57:27,587
But I'll just take planning as an example.

508
00:57:28,367 --> 00:57:37,494
If nobody has a question that there's any sort of planning inconsistency or problem with planning, it's not an issue and it doesn't need to be part of the board's deliberations.

509
00:57:39,013 --> 00:57:42,594
If planning is a big concern, then that's a different matter.

510
00:57:43,234 --> 00:57:56,798
But it really is, that's the sort of topic where the city staff would be in the best position to sort of lead the discussion around about the city's planning objectives and how the project may or may not fit those.

511
00:57:57,658 --> 00:57:59,659
You don't need a peer review consultant for that.

512
00:58:00,980 --> 00:58:15,960
And, you know, it's pretty typical for a board to look at the things that sort of matter the most significantly in terms of the quality of life for people who are going to live in a development, public health, public safety, environmental impact, and

513
00:58:17,949 --> 00:58:19,650
transportation or traffic as part of that.

514
00:58:20,610 --> 00:58:23,872
Those tend to be kind of big issues with these bigger projects.

515
00:58:24,552 --> 00:58:28,975
But things like planning or open space, not necessarily.

516
00:58:29,115 --> 00:58:34,837
If the project satisfies the board's desires, then that's done.

517
00:58:35,018 --> 00:58:39,560
And now you focus on the things that are the issues that really are disturbing to the board.

518
00:58:40,100 --> 00:58:43,282
You guys get to decide what the agenda is.

519
00:58:44,421 --> 00:58:51,947
